{"lemma":"مُطَبَّقَةٍ","slug":"مُطَبَّقَةٍ","root":"ط.ب.ق","root_slug":"ط-ب-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ب-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26355","n26356","n26357","n26358"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wrap (a type of food)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of stuffed pancake, mutabbaq"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a kind of pan-fried bread, mutabbaq"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"observing, applying"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"observed, applied"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"applicable, effective"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"passive participle of أَطْبَقَ (ʔaṭbaqa)","tags":["form-of","participle","passive"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"velarized","examples":[{"text":"Sibawayh ((Can we date this quote?)), “باب عدد الحروف العربية ومخارجها ومهموسها ومجهورها وأحوال مهموسها ومجهورها واختلافها”, in Al-Kitab\nوَمِنْهَا ٱلْمُطْبَقَةُ وَٱلْمُنْفَتِحَةُ. فَأَمَّا ٱلْمُطْبَقَةُ فَٱلصَّادُ، وَٱلضَّادُ، وَٱلطَّاءُ، وَٱلظَّاءُ. وَٱلْمُنْفَتِحَةُ: كُلُّ مَا سِوَى ذٰلِكَ مِنَ ٱلْحُرُوفِ؛ لِأَنَّكَ لَا تُطْبِقُ لِشَيْءٍ مِنْهُنَّ لِسَانَكَ، تَرْفَعُهُ إِلَى ٱلْحَنَكِ ٱلْأَعْلَى. وَهٰذِهِ ٱلْحُرُوفُ ٱلْأَرْبَعَةُ إِذَا وَضَعْتَ لِسَانَكَ فِي مَوَاضِعِهِنَّ ٱنْطَبَقَ لِسَانُكَ مِنْ مَوَاضِعِهِنَّ إِلَى مَا حَاذَى ٱلْحَنَكَ ٱلْأَعْلَى مِنَ ٱللِّسَانِ تَرْفَعُهُ إِلَى ٱلْحَنَكِ، فَإِذَا وَضَعْتَ لِسَانَكَ فَٱلصَّوْتُ مَحْصُورٌ فِيمَا بَيْنَ ٱللِّسَانِ وَٱلْحَنَكِ إِلَى مَوْضِعِ ٱلْحُرُوفِ.\nwaminhā l-muṭbaqatu wal-munfatiḥatu. faʔammā l-muṭbaqatu faṣ-ṣādu, waḍ-ḍādu, waṭ-ṭāʔu, waẓ-ẓāʔu. wal-munfatiḥatu: kullu mā siwā ḏālika mina l-ḥurūfi; liʔannaka lā tuṭbiqu lišayʔin minhunna lisānaka, tarfaʕuhu ʔilā l-ḥanaki l-ʔaʕlā. wahāḏihi l-ḥurūfu l-ʔarbaʕatu ʔiḏā waḍaʕta lisānaka fī mawāḍiʕihinna nṭabaqa lisānuka min mawāḍiʕihinna ʔilā mā ḥāḏā l-ḥanaka l-ʔaʕlā mina l-lisāni tarfaʕuhu ʔilā l-ḥanaki, faʔiḏā waḍaʕta lisānaka faṣ-ṣawtu maḥṣūrun fīmā bayna l-lisāni wal-ḥanaki ʔilā mawḍiʕi l-ḥurūfi.","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle from طَبَّقَ (ṭabbaqa).\n\nDerived from the active participle from طَبَّقَ (ṭabbaqa)."},"ipa":["/mu.tˤab.baq/","/mu.tˤab.baɡ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26355","headword_ar":"مَطْبَقٌ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobiqN","text_ar":"مُطْبِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26356","headword_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. part. n. of 4,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Covered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHuruwfu AlmuTobaqapu","text_ar":"الحُرُوفُ المُطْبَقَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The letters"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"T","text_ar":"ط"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) the part of the tongue which is the place of their utterance being [closely] covered [in their utterance] by what is opposite to it of the palate. (O, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1828},{"kind":"text","text":"used by the vulgar for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN Ealayohi","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN Ealayohi Aljunuwnu","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ عَلَيْهِ الجُنُونُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon whom insanity is made to be continual:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb: see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TabaAqaA='u","text_ar":"طَبَاقَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[where"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN Ealoyahi","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ عَلْيَهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in my opinion better rendered]:) and you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majonuwnapN muTobaqN EalayohaA","text_ar":"مَجْنُونَةٌ مُطْبَقٌ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in like manner, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN EalayohaA Aljunuwnu","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ عَلَيْهَا الجُنُونُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an insane female whose reason insanity has veiled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wholly obscured"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, O.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN Ealayohi","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Affected with a swooning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fit of insensibility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayotN muTobaqN","text_ar":"بَيْتٌ مُطْبَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A verse of which the former hemistich ends in the middle of a word."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.) ―         -b6-  See also the next paragraph. ―         -b7-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiboqN","text_ar":"طِبْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K"]},{"entry_id":"n26357","headword_ar":"مُطْبِقٌ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Covering."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"junuwnN muTobiqN","text_ar":"جُنُونٌ مُطْبِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, O, K, TA) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Insanity that covers"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"veils,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wholly obscures,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the reason,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~aY muTobiqapN","text_ar":"حُمَّى مُطْبِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A continual fever, not quitting night nor day."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, * TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobiqapN","text_ar":"مُطْبِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanapN muTobiqapN","text_ar":"سَنَةٌ مُطْبِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"severe, year."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobiqaAtN","text_ar":"مُطْبِقَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Calamities"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaAtu TabaqK","text_ar":"بَنَاتُ طَبَقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobiqN","text_ar":"مُطْبِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"may have the same meaning as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobaqN","text_ar":"مُطْبَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [But in what sense the latter is here used is not specified.]) ―         -b6-  It signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A subterranean prison;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of confinement beneath the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [The word in this sense, which is probably postclassical, is there said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHosinN","text_ar":"مُحْسِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but perhaps only because of its having been found written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTobiqN","text_ar":"مُطْبِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for I think that I have heard ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTobaqN","text_ar":"مَطْبَقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"used in this sense; and I find an apparent authority for this in a copy of the M in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASd","text_ar":"اصد"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wSd","text_ar":"وصد"},{"kind":"text","text":", where"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iSaAdu","text_ar":"الاـِصَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwiSaAdu","text_ar":"الوِصَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaTobaqu","text_ar":"المَطْبَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and likewise in the TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"En","text_ar":"عن"},{"kind":"text","text":", where I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTobaq","text_ar":"مَطْبَق"},{"kind":"text","text":", thus written; see 2 in that art.: it seems also that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TibaAqN","text_ar":"طِبَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"may have the same signification; for I find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_iSaAdu","text_ar":"الاـِصَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ibaAqu","text_ar":"الطِّبَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASd","text_ar":"اصد"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and thus in the O in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wSd","text_ar":"وصد"},{"kind":"text","text":", and likewise"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlwiSaAdu","text_ar":"الوِصَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Mgh","O","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n26358","headword_ar":"مُطَبَّقٌ","root":"Tbq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiboqN","text_ar":"طِبْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}